    "thumbnail_filename": "saints_thumbnail_video_17.png",
    "title": "The Monk Who Crossed the World to Protect Alaska (Icon-Only Review Draft)",
    "description": "The story begins far from the centers of power. Not in Moscow, not in Rome, not in a cathedral full of gold, but on a cold island in Alaska, where the sea could swallow a boat, where winter pressed against the windows, and where a quiet monk became a father to people others treated as expendable.\n\nThis reverent documentary tells the story through Orthodox witness and tradition, with careful attention to sources, humility, repentance, miracles, and grace.\n\nQuestion for viewers: what part of this story stayed with you most?\n\nThe Saints is a documentary channel about Orthodox and Catholic saints, elders, monks, miracles, repentance, courage, and grace.",
