    "thumbnail_filename": "saints_thumbnail_video_13.png",
    "title": "Saint Ambrose of Optina: The Elder Who Answered Two Hundred Souls a Day",
    "description": "Saint Ambrose of Optina became one of Russia's most beloved elders, receiving crowds of people who came with grief, confusion, sin, illness, and impossible decisions.\nThis reverent documentary tells his life as witness and tradition: the sick monk whose weakness became a doorway for mercy, discernment, and spiritual healing.\n\nChapters:\n0:00 The Line Outside the Cell\n0:48 The Promise He Tried to Forget\n1:40 What an Elder Really Was\n2:30 The Daily Martyrdom of Counsel\n3:23 Letters as Conversations\n4:07 The Writer Who Came in Grief\n4:51 Seeing the Person, Not the Problem\n5:36 Weakness That Became Strength\n6:10 The Spiritual Hospital\n6:48 The Door Still Opens\n\nThe Saints is a documentary channel about Orthodox and Catholic saints, elders, monks, miracles, repentance, courage, and grace.\nSubscribe for more stories from Optina Pustyn, Mount Athos, Russia, Alaska, and the ancient Christian world.",
