    "title": "Saint Paisios of Mount Athos: The Monk Who Told the Modern World to Thirst for God",
    "description": "Saint Paisios of Mount Athos lived in poverty, silence, and prayer, yet modern pilgrims climbed the rough path to his cell carrying grief, fear, confusion, and spiritual thirst.\nThis reverent documentary tells his life and counsel as Orthodox witness and tradition: exile, Mount Athos, discernment, miracles remembered by pilgrims, and the question he still asks the modern world.\n\nThe Saints is a documentary channel about Orthodox and Catholic saints, elders, monks, miracles, repentance, courage, and grace.",
