    "title": "Saint Silouan: The Monk Who Survived Despair",
    "description": "Saint Silouan the Athonite passed through a spiritual darkness so severe that one sentence became his path through pride and despair: keep your mind in hell, and despair not.\nThis reverent documentary tells his life as Orthodox witness and tradition: Russia, Mount Athos, prayer for enemies, Saint Sophrony preserving his memory, and why his teaching still speaks to modern despair.\n\nQuestion for viewers: where do you see the difference between humility and hopelessness?\n\nThe Saints is a documentary channel about Orthodox and Catholic saints, elders, monks, miracles, repentance, courage, and grace.",
